& [ConversationFrontierLifecycleBoundaryDesign] is the design boundary for active work frontier versus run lifecycle status
  @ [created_at] 2026-05-30T15:02:00Z
  @ [triggering_slice] S284_narrative_coverage_after_prelive_recipe_reference
  @ [related_file] src/negotiated_agent/orchestrator.py
  @ [related_file] src/negotiated_agent/conversation.py
  @ [related_evidence] coordination/narrative_stale_check.sop

  + [problem] is orchestrator run lifecycle updates currently write transient run status phrases into current_frontier
  + [problem] is narrative stale-check treats current_frontier as the active work-slice frontier and can therefore request narrative updates for run completion phrases
  + [decision] is current_frontier must remain the active work-slice frontier or explicit frontier advancement target
  + [decision] is run lifecycle state should be recorded in run_lifecycle_frontier and last_proof fields instead
  + [decision] is long-run checkpoint may read end_run_lifecycle_frontier separately from current_frontier when it wants to summarize a just-completed dry run
  + [authority_boundary] is lifecycle_status_not_work_frontier

& [FieldSemantics] is the target conversation surface vocabulary
  + [field] is current_frontier
  + [meaning] is the current slice/frontier that future Codex work should resume from
  + [writer] is Manager notice updates, frontier application helpers, or explicit operator/agent frontier advancement
  + [non_writer] is ordinary dry-run lifecycle events

  + [field] is run_lifecycle_frontier
  + [meaning] is the latest transient NegotiatedCodingAgent run milestone such as run started approved layer wrote implementation or completed
  + [writer] is orchestrator run lifecycle updates
  + [reader] is checkpoint and narrative proof tools that need run status context

& [ImplementationDirection] is the next safe code slice
  + [slice] is replace orchestrator conversation updates so run lifecycle calls write run_lifecycle_frontier while preserving last_proof
  + [slice] is update long-run checkpoint end frontier naming so it can report end_run_lifecycle_frontier without overwriting active current_frontier semantics
  + [slice] is update tests that currently expect completed run text in current_frontier
  + [slice] is keep blocked run repair breadcrumbs as run_lifecycle_frontier unless a separate explicit frontier advancement is written

& [AcceptanceCriteria] is how to prove the boundary
  + [criterion] is dry-run lifecycle update leaves current_frontier unchanged when it starts from a slice id
  + [criterion] is dry-run lifecycle update writes run_lifecycle_frontier with the run status phrase
  + [criterion] is narrative stale-check reads current_frontier as a slice id and does not request updates for run lifecycle phrases
  + [criterion] is checkpoint records run lifecycle status separately from active work frontier
